      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARTIE'S ECLIPSE (4) has been racing in much stronger company than this in recent efforts and should appreciate the drop in grade. She was a little disappointing last time out at Ascot but that effort still stacks right up. Can get back to her best now and pick up her maiden win. DEW TELL (10) was tested in much stronger company last start where she was outclassed. Back to a more suitable race today with the claim of Webster coming in handy. Drawn nicely and can improve sharply. LONGTIMEBELIEVER (5) is still a maiden after 14 runs. Was one of the favoured runners last time out but didn't live up to market expectations, finishing eighth over 1100m at Albany. Looks to be in the right race to play a big role. SNIPELISA (7) debuted three weeks ago when she finished ninth over 1200m at Pinjarra, beaten 5.5 lengths. Will be better for that run and is expected to go well. FLICK'N RUBIES (9) gets the blinkers on today on the quick turnaround and can't be discounted.",
